S \subset L^2(\mathbb{R})
S^{\perp} =\{f \in L^2(\mathbb R) | \left< f,g\right> =0, g \in S\}
S^{\perp}
L^2
S^\bot = \lbrace f \in L^2| \int_\mathbb{R} fg dx = 0 , \forall g \in S \rbrace
L^2
f, g  \in S^\bot
\alpha, \beta \in \mathbb{R}
h \in S
\int_\mathbb{R} (\alpha f + \beta g)h dx = \alpha\int_\mathbb{R}fh dx + \beta\int_\mathbb{R}gh dx = \alpha 0 + \beta 0 = 0
\alpha f + \beta g \in S^\top
S^\bot
